OL,3,C'I actually heard the blast': 40th
OL,4,Canniversary of IRA Brighton bomb
OL,6,FThere were several receptions with
OL,7,Flots of free booze and an opportunity
OL,8,Ffor journalists like me to mingle and
OL,9,Fnetwork with senior members of the
OL,10,Fgovernment and officials who could be
OL,11,Fuseful to know.
OL,13,FSo that is how I came to still be up
OL,14,Fand in a bar a few doors from the
OL,15,FGrand Hotel when an IRA bomb, planted
OL,16,Fa few weeks earlier, was detonated at
OL,17,F2.54am.
OL,19,FIt was the hotel where then Prime
OL,20,FMinister Margaret Thatcher and her
OL,21,Fgovernment colleagues were staying.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
