OL,3,C'I actually heard the blast': 40th
OL,4,Canniversary of IRA Brighton bomb
OL,6,FThe tools of their trade were locked
OL,7,Faway and there was no time to go
OL,8,Flooking for keys, so we broke into ITN
OL,9,Fcars and a secure portacabin to grab
OL,10,Fthe camera and recording equipment we
OL,11,Fwould need.
OL,13,FWithin minutes of the explosion - and
OL,14,Fbefore the police had time to respond
OL,15,Fby throwing a cordon around the scene
OL,16,Fof the crime - we were in the hotel
OL,17,Fentrance seeing dust covered survivors
OL,18,Fincluding senior ministers stagger out
OL,19,Fonto the seafront.
OL,21,FMost were clearly in a state of shock.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
